  <li>先々週(せんせんしゅう</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="月">月</h4>
<ol>
  <li>一ヶ月(いっかげつ)</li>
  <li>六ヶ月(ろっかげつ)</li>
  <li>十ヶ月(じゅっかげつ)</li>
  <li>先々月</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="年">年</h4>
<ol>
  <li>年末(ねんまつ) 今年 去年 来年</li>
  <li>年度: 来年度の予算</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="counting-and-counters">counting and counters</h4>
<p>月 <br /></p>
<ol>
  <li>April 四月(しがつ)</li>
  <li>July  七月(しちがつ)</li>
  <li>September 九月(くがつ)
日 <br />
<img src="/images/japanese-date.png" />
分<br /></li>
  <li>1分(いっぷん)</li>
  <li>3分(さんぷん)</li>
  <li>4分(よんぷん)</li>
  <li>6分(ろっぷん)</li>
  <li>8分(はっぷん)</li>
  <li>10分(じゅっぷん)
週<br /></li>
  <li>8週間(はっしゅうかん)
月 the small [ヶ] is totally different from ケ, it is the abbrevation for the kanji[箇]<br /></li>
</ol>

<p>a span of time <br />
The basic counter for a span of time is [間] which is read as [かん]</p>
<ol>
  <li>you can attach it to the end of hours, days, weeks, and years.</li>
  <li>minutes and second do not need this counter and month has a seperate counter.</li>
  <li>二時間40分(にじかんよんじゅっぷん)</li>
  <li>二十日間(はつかかん)</li>
  <li>15日間(じゅうごにちかん)</li>
  <li>二年間(にねんかん)</li>
  <li>一日(いちにち)</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="目-to-show-order">目 to show order</h4>
<p>you can attach [目] to different counters to show order. <br />
例えば、[一番] which means number one becomes the first when you add <a href="一番目">目</a></p>
<ol>
  <li>1回目　the first time</li>
  <li>四人目 the fourth person</li>
</ol>

